<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/477> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #477" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 5.13.3; Diod. 14.54.1; Fast. Cap. (see note 1); Chr. 354 (Augurino et Longo); Degrassi 28f., 99, 382f. According to Livy (5.13.3), Veturius was the only patrician in this college." ;
	dprr:hasID 477 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/476> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #476" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The names are preserved as follows in Fast. Cap.: [Cn. Genu]cius, etc., [L. Atiliu]s, etc., [M. Pomp]onius, etc., the rest entire as above except Vetur[i]us, and Po[b]lilius. In Livy Duillius has the praenomen Cn., but C. is indicated in Fast. Cap. and Diod. ({Gr}). Livy's reading Publicius is corrected from 2.55.4, and Fast. Cap. Diod. has {Gr}, with the variants {Gr} P and {Gr} F. Diod. and Fast. Cap. agree against Livy on the order of names given above." ;
	dprr:hasID 476 .
